{title: Wedding Cake}
{artist: Connie Smith}
{composer: Written by Myra Smith and Margaret Lewis}

Don't think you failed me cause you can't afford
That dishwasher to make my life more [C]fun
You know the [C7]measure of a man is much more
Than just the money he can [F]make
And every [C]woman knows a lot of joy
And [G7]tears come with the wedding [C]cake
The wedding cake is not all icing
And loving tender whispers in the [G7]dark
One slice is concern for all your dreams
Afraid they won't come true and [C]break your heart
