Crying when the [F]doorbell rings and there are [Fm]roses
Every [C]woman knows a lot of give
And [G7]take comes with the wedding [C]cake
It's facing shadows of the future prayin' they will fall away
As we walk towards them searching for the [G7]sun
And it's long and anxious hours with the wolf at the door
Hugs and kisses when at last we see the [C]dawn
So when the hands of time trace tiny lines
